      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;shraddhanjali-sabha-of-mahamahopadhyaya-shri-k-s-varadacharya&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shraddhanjali Sabha of Mahamahopadhyaya Shri K. S. Varadacharya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;![][image1] From &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o_iNRq897i4&#34;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o_iNRq897i4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This assembly (&lt;em&gt;Shraddhanjali Sabha&lt;/em&gt;) marks the physical departure and celebrates the enduring intellectual and spiritual legacy of &lt;strong&gt;Mahamahopadhyaya Shri K. S. Varadacharya (KSV)&lt;/strong&gt; (1921–2020), a scholar who represented the pinnacle of &lt;em&gt;Ubhaya Vedanta&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;Nyaya&lt;/em&gt;, and &lt;em&gt;Vyakarana&lt;/em&gt; in the modern era. Organized by his disciples from Nepal and India, the memorial brought together preeminent heads of monasteries (&lt;em&gt;Mathadhipatis&lt;/em&gt;) across sectarian lines, university vice-chancellors, and traditional scholars.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
